> [@learningcoding-pixel](https://github.com/learningcoding-pixel) There is a chance that the `gitmastery` command is hitting a different file than the intended `gitmastery.exe`. I suggest the following:
> 
> 1. Delete any files that has `gitmastery` in your `Downloads` folder.
> 2. Remove `Downloads` from the `PATH`. It is not a good idea to put in the `PATH` as that is a location where all sorts of files will arrive from the Internet.
> 3. Restart git-bash. Run `gitmastery --help` to ensure it can't find the file to run (i.e., gitmastery is no longer in the `PATH`)
> 4. Download `gitmastery.exe` again. Ensure it has the `.exe` extension.
> 5. Move it to some other location e.g., `/c/Users/yinwe/Apps`. Add that folder to the `PATH`.
> 6. Restart `git-bash` and try again

