I am curious, what troubles did you have with implementation?

As for the implementation, we should never crash the program. 
As mentioned I would catch it in the callee, and then like you said, propagate an error message up.
This way if the end user expects output, you could still see something general while not revealing too much of your backend like 
"Error connecting with database, check your connection" 

I think it also goes beyond code and efficiency as I mentioned (and as such what you refer to as "which solution fits best for your use case")
To me code readability is important especially when you are working in a team.
For example in python, I would rather see a "normal" embedded for loop than a 3 tier list comprehension even if list comprehension is much more efficient. 

