Snippet of `deadline` switch case for my `.parse` function for my `InputParser` class
You can see that only if after all the checks did not break (i.e. it has no issues) then will I actually call `getTaskName` and the likes


```
        case "deadline":
            if (argKeywordNotFound(wordsList, "/by", command)) ``{``
                break;
            ``}``
            if (taskNameNotFound(wordsList,"/by", command)) ``{``
                break;
            ``}``
            if (noArgSupplied(wordsList, List.of("/by"),
                    "/by", "date", command)) ``{``
                break;
            ``}``
            taskName = getTaskName(wordsList, "/by");
            taskArg = getArg(wordsList, "/by","" );
            dateType = validDateType(taskArg);
            if (Objects.equals(dateType, ""))``{``
                break;
            ``}``
            argsList.add(taskArg);
            this.taskManager.addTask(command, taskName, argsList, isMarked, dateType);
            break;
```

`argKeywordNotFound` function
```
    private boolean argKeywordNotFound(List<String> wordsList, String argKeyword, String command)``{``
        // We are assuming command has already been verified.
        if (!wordsList.contains(argKeyword)) ``{``
            this.uiError.displayArgKeywordNotFound(argKeyword, command);
            return true;
        ``}``
        return false;
    ``}``
```

Although `validDateType` has a good few meaningful test cases, most of the functions are super atomic, so a test case would just be one positive (where the `argKeyword` is in the `wordsList`, maybe there could be two instances and it would be positive as well) and a negative test (where  `argKeyword` is not in the `wordsList`). 
And even then for the duplicated case, I would just add it as another function to check.
So there is not much space for meaningful tests.

A more meaningful test would probably be testing the actual switch cases, however that goes against a unit test based on my understanding. There is also no return available (task gets added).

Also, typing it out I just realized, most of the checker functions are private as well.
Only real solution i can think of is to use mocks to track that certain functions are called with certain arguments

</panel>

