I think one reason could be because the concept is mainly conceptual compared to composition which is practical and enforceable -- what i mean by conceptual is when we say the part **can** exist independently from the whole, it makes it unclear how we should deal with the part and if it really exists independently eg. Library aggregates book - can book exist independently from library? maybe yes, but what does the diagram intend for us to do with that information? The diagram does not specify what that means for ownership or lifecycle, so in this sense it does not really add much value. I think using association or composition to clarify relationships can be clearer
