<panel  popup-url="https://github.com/nus-cs2103-AY2526S1/forum/issues/137" expanded>
<div slot="header">

**1. :fas-info-circle: CheckStyle wants lambda expressions brackets to be line separated**
</div>

The line :
```
 <module name="SeparatorWrap">
      &gt;!-- Checks that the ",", "]", "[", "...", ";", "(" is at the previous end of line in a line wrap. -->
      <property name="tokens" value="COMMA, RBRACK, ARRAY_DECLARATOR, ELLIPSIS, SEMI, LPAREN"/>
      <property name="option" value="eol"/>
    </module>
```
in checkstyle.xml makes the code:
```
        InvalidTaskTypeException exception = assertThrows(
                InvalidTaskTypeException.class,
                () -&gt; Task.fromString(taskString)); // error on this line
```
to have a separatorWrap error when running checkstyle, because the lambda expression's brackets aren't separated by a line.

It seems that this isn't expected behaviour considering that Google's Java Style Guide also states that:
<img width="1185" height="341" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/afe3c4f1-ff11-4c66-8d21-dd61c319185e" />
> A line is never broken adjacent to the arrow in a lambda" - This means you should NOT break the line right before or after the -&gt; arrow.
1. Is this expected behaviour
2. If so, has anyone found a way to get their java formatter to format it like so:
```
(
) -&gt; Someclass.doSomething()
```

If not, are we allowed to edit the checkstyle.xml to stop this from throwing an error
</panel>

