<panel  popup-url="https://github.com/nus-cs2103-AY2526S1/forum/issues/15#issuecomment-3176320123" expanded>
<div slot="header">

**2 :fas-comment:**
</div>

Never mind, resolved. 

User error.

I had mistakenly added the directory as a new system variable 'gitmastery', instead of editing the existing 'Path' system variable and adding a new line to it. 

I also should have run .\gitmastery.exe on Powershell and ./gitmastery.exe on Git Bash instead of gitmastery,exe directly. but after adding the gitmastery-home directory to Path properly it can run properly without prefixing with ./ or .\ anymore.

Sorry for the inconvenience!

<img width="1595" height="642" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/074e09f5-d53a-43c6-a318-028ebfecf8e9" />
