<panel type="info"  collapsed>
<div slot="header">

### 89. CHON..PHER `@christopherchong` (1 posts) 
</div>


<panel  popup-url="https://github.com/nus-cs2103-AY2526S1/forum/issues/82#issuecomment-3228373636" expanded>
<div slot="header">

**1 :fas-comment:**
</div>

I have shifted from using text-ui-test (input.txt and expected.txt) to JUnit for a more automated testing approach. 

text-ui-test was useful before saving was implemented as there was no memory involved so outputs were always consistent. However, with the introduction of a file to save to and load from, it is more practical to utilize JUnit for future testing as it allows you to test individual features in a more stable and automated manner. 
</panel>

</panel>


