### 131. LEE ..NWON `@NownuJ` (1 posts) 
</div>


<panel  popup-url="https://github.com/nus-cs2103-AY2526S1/forum/issues/87#issuecomment-3232622059" expanded>
<div slot="header">

**1 :fas-comment:**
</div>

I separated my commands from the parser. While they are closely related and storing the commands in the parser is a form of encapsulation, the script may become unmanageable once you start having more commands to keep track of.  In addition, I find it easier to debug or change them in the future when each command is in a separate script.
</panel>

